  {
   "id": "idc-instance",
   "service": "management/iam-identity-center",
   "enabled": false,
   "heavy": true,
   "_note": "SSO (IAM Identity Center) INSTANCE lifecycle. BLAST RADIUS: an SSO instance is account-structural — creating/patching/deleting one on a shared account is sensitive and may be irreversible (it backs all SSO users/groups/permission-sets). Therefore heavy + every mutating step optional with broad expect_status so an expected 403/400/409/422 RECORDS coverage WITHOUT creating real SSO structure or failing the run. POST body from data/api_bodies.json (createinstance, ACTIVE_DIRECTORY identity_store_config). PATCH body from setinstance (method confirmed PATCH from catalog). instance_id captured from create if it ever succeeds; otherwise PATCH/DELETE fire against the captured id only when present (group isolation). The single-instance show GET is probed. Response envelope for the instance id is UNPROVEN — guessed $.instance.id with soft fallbacks; mark unverified. | DISABLED 2026-06-10: service excluded from C3 target (owner decision; waived in coverage_waivers.json).",
   "steps": [
    {
     "name": "create-instance",
     "method": "POST",
     "path": "/v1/instances",
     "group": "idc-instance",
     "optional": true,
     "json": {
      "name": "regridc{ualpha}",
      "description": "API regression suite SSO instance",
      "identity_store_type": "ACTIVE_DIRECTORY",
      "identity_store_config": {
       "bind_credential": "password",
       "bind_dn": "CN=Administrator,CN=Users,DC=test,DC=add",
       "connection_url": "ldaps://test.subdomain.company.com:123",
       "rdn_ldap_attribute": "cn",
       "user_object_classes": "person, organizationalPerson, user",
       "username_ldap_attribute": "sAMAccountName",
       "users_dn": "OU=Employees,OU=Accounts,DC=sub,DC=org"
      }
     },
     "expect_status": [
      200,
      201,
      202,
      400,
      403,
      404,
      409,
      422
     ],
     "capture_soft": {
      "instance_id": "$.instance.id"
     },
     "cleanup": {
      "method": "DELETE",
      "path": "/v1/instances/{instance_id}",
      "service": "iam-identity-center"
     },
     "_note": "Capture is SOFT: if the create is denied (likely on a shared account) the lifecycle still records the POST and moves on without a real id."
    },
    {
     "name": "list-instances",
     "method": "GET",
     "path": "/v1/instances",
     "group": "idc-instance",
     "optional": true,
     "expect_status": [
      200,
      403,
      404
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "patch-instance",
     "method": "PATCH",
     "path": "/v1/instances/{instance_id}",
     "service": "iam-identity-center",
     "group": "idc-instance",
     "optional": true,
     "json": {
      "name": "regridc{ualpha}",
      "description": "updated by API regression suite",
      "identity_store_type": "IDENTITY_CENTER_DIRECTORY"
     },
     "expect_status": [
      200,
      202,
      400,
      403,
      404,
      409,
      422
     ],
     "_note": "Fires only if create captured an instance_id (group isolated); records the PATCH /v1/instances/{instance_id} write either way once called."
    },
    {
     "name": "probe-reads",
     "probe_reads": {
      "instance_id": "{instance_id}"
     }
    },
    {
     "name": "delete-instance",
     "method": "DELETE",
     "path": "/v1/instances/{instance_id}",
     "service": "iam-identity-center",
     "group": "idc-instance",
